  <activity
      android:name="androidx.health.connect.client.impl.platform.impl.HealthConnectClientUpsideDownCakeImpl$HealthConnectPermissionActivity"
      android:exported="false" />

  NOTE: The @kiwi-health/capacitor-health-connect plugin also merges its own
  manifest fragment automatically via the plugin manifest, so the rationale
  activity may already be present after `npx cap sync`.

  ── 4. DEEP LINKS for OAuth callbacks ────────────────────────────────────────
  If you want OAuth redirects (Strava, YNAB, Truelayer) to open in-app rather
  than in an external browser, add an intent-filter to the main activity:

  <intent-filter android:autoVerify="true">
    <action android:name="android.intent.action.VIEW" />
    <category android:name="android.intent.category.DEFAULT" />
    <category android:name="android.intent.category.BROWSABLE" />
    <data android:scheme="https"
          android:host="YOUR_VERCEL_DOMAIN"
          android:pathPrefix="/api/strava/callback" />
    <data android:scheme="https"
          android:host="YOUR_VERCEL_DOMAIN"
          android:pathPrefix="/api/ynab/callback" />
    <data android:scheme="https"
          android:host="YOUR_VERCEL_DOMAIN"
          android:pathPrefix="/api/truelayer/callback" />
  </intent-filter>

  Replace YOUR_VERCEL_DOMAIN with your actual domain (e.g. emergenthealth.app).
  Then verify domain ownership via Digital Asset Links:
  https://developer.android.com/training/app-links/verify-android-applinks
-->
</content>
</invoke>